The '''Central Institute of Buddhist Studies''', formerly known as the School of Buddhist Philosophy, is an educational institute located in [[Leh]]. It was founded in 1959 and is affiliated to the Sampurnanand Sanskrit University of Varanasi. Apart from Buddhist Philosophy Sanskrit, English, Hindi, Tibetan and Pali languages are also taught.<ref name="india9">{{cite web|url=http://www.india9.com/i9show/Central-Institute-of-Buddhist-Studies-58004.htm|title=Central Institute of Buddhist Studies in Leh India|publisher=india9.com|accessdate=2014-09-18}}</ref>
